---
// Short read: UPI by state (compliant choropleth). Data: state-wise.json.
// Map: public/maps/india_states.json (J&K/Ladakh/Arunachal per india-official-geojson).
import ReadLayout from '../../../components/read/ReadLayout.astro';
import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';
import { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';

const raw = JSON.parse(readFileSync(fileURLToPath(new URL('../../../../public/data/economy/state-wise.json', import.meta.url)), 'utf8'));
const rows = raw.rows ?? raw;
const months = [...new Set(rows.map((r: any) => r.month))].sort();
const lm = months[months.length - 1];
const latest = rows.filter((r: any) => r.month === lm);
const tot = latest.reduce((a: number, r: any) => a + (r.volume_cr || 0), 0);
const sorted = [...latest].sort((a, b) => b.volume_cr - a.volume_cr);
const MONTHS = ['', 'January', 'February', 'March', 'April', 'May', 'June', 'July', 'August', 'September', 'October', 'November', 'December'];
const title2 = (s: string) => s.split(' ').map((w) => w[0] + w.slice(1).toLowerCase()).join(' ');
const stats = {
  asOf: `${MONTHS[+lm.split('-')[1]]} ${lm.split('-')[0]}`,
  top: title2(sorted[0].state), topShare: Math.round(100 * sorted[0].volume_cr / tot),
  top5: Math.round(100 * sorted.slice(0, 5).reduce((a, r) => a + r.volume_cr, 0) / tot),
  top10: Math.round(100 * sorted.slice(0, 10).reduce((a, r) => a + r.volume_cr, 0) / tot),
};
const payload = JSON.stringify({ rows: latest });
---

<ReadLayout
  slug="where-india-pays"
  kicker="Economy · Monthly"
  asOf={stats.asOf}
  units={true}
>
  <figure class="chartfig wide">
    <div class="chart" id="read-chart" style="height:480px"></div>
    <figcaption>UPI transactions by state, {stats.asOf}. Boundaries: <a href="https://github.com/AbhinavSwami28/india-official-geojson">india-official-geojson</a> (MIT), per the Government of India position. Data: NPCI.</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <div class="prose">
    <p>UPI is everywhere, but not evenly. The map shows where the payments actually originate, and a
      handful of states do most of the work. <strong>{stats.top}</strong> alone accounts for about
      <strong>{stats.topShare}%</strong> of all UPI volume. The top five states together make up
      roughly <strong>{stats.top5}%</strong>, and the top ten about <strong>{stats.top10}%</strong>.</p>
    <p>The leaders cluster in the west and south, India’s richer, more urban, more banked regions:
      Maharashtra, Karnataka, Telangana, Tamil Nadu. The big exception is Uttar Pradesh, which ranks
      high on sheer population even though each person there pays less often than in the southern
      states.</p>

    <div class="pullstat">
      <div><span class="n">{stats.top5}%</span><span class="l">of UPI comes from the <em>top five</em> states</span></div>
      <div><span class="n">{stats.topShare}%</span><span class="l">from <em>{stats.top}</em> alone</span></div>
    </div>

    <p>One caveat worth keeping in mind: this is total volume, which naturally tracks population and
      income. Measured per person the map would shift, with small, urban states and union territories
      punching above their weight and the poorer, more rural states trailing. Those trailing states
      are where UPI’s next leg of growth has to come from.</p>

    <p class="source">Source: NPCI state-wise UPI statistics, processed by Time Series of India.
      Map boundaries via <a href="https://github.com/AbhinavSwami28/india-official-geojson">india-official-geojson</a> (MIT).
      <a href="/economy/dashboards/state-wise">Explore the dashboard →</a></p>
  </div>

  <script type="application/json" id="read-data" set:html={payload}></script>
</ReadLayout>

<script>
  import * as echarts from 'echarts';
  import { buildPanel, readTokens } from '../../../lib/dashboards/runtime';
  import type { PanelSpec, CtrlState } from '../../../lib/dashboards/runtime';

  const data = JSON.parse(document.getElementById('read-data')!.textContent!);
  const host = document.getElementById('read-chart');
  if (host) {
    (async () => {
      const geo = await fetch('/maps/india_states.json').then((r) => r.json());
      echarts.registerMap('india', geo);
      const spec: PanelSpec = { id: 'states', title: '', chart: 'choropleth', map: 'india', encoding: { region: 'state', y: 'volume_cr' } };
      const chart = echarts.init(host);
      const render = () => chart.setOption(buildPanel(spec, data.rows, { metric: 'volume_cr' } as CtrlState, readTokens()), true);
      new ResizeObserver(() => chart.resize()).observe(host);
      new MutationObserver(render).observe(document.documentElement, { attributes: true, attributeFilter: ['data-theme', 'data-units'] });
      render();
      document.fonts?.ready.then(render);
    })();
  }
</script>
